replies.body:
What a rood dude. Attach logs as attachments; don't copy-paste all the data.

Anyway, have you disabled automatic updates and maintenance on your new laptop?
ill try that now it seems to be disappearing the more i play use to be every 2 mins now its 10mins ill get a 300ping spike and it will last about 15secs

Check the automatic updates you may have enabled for other, if not *all* the programs on your computer. Each one is unique.

You can also try shutting off unnecessary services that may connect to the internet, such as iTunes or Google Chrome (they run in the background even if you press X on them).

so after trying everything suggested + i few tricks picked up off googling, it  seems to have disappeared. i get the occasional 10 ping jump every 20mins im unsure what fixed it since i did so many at once but running a windows update disabling maintenance a few services and processes with the fact some  how i bought a "gaming laptop" that had the option set adjust best performance for background services instead of programs by default is beyond me, which is what i think was the actual problem in the end. thank you for your suggestions anyway guys :D

>settings from within the OS UI

lol

Anyway, happy to see that you've fixed your lag. Happy gaming!

i just bought a new laptop that has windows 8.1 installed the game spikes every 2 min or so from 50 ping to 400-500 then gradually drops back down to 50 
so i decided to run my old laptop in a bot game at the same time with my new one 
my new laptop ping spikes from 50-400 while the older laptop next to it doesnt spike at all and gives a constant 50 
can someone explain why this might be
